content: Set up a local development environment for Xander. It's basic now, but the foundation is laid. Learning curve is steep but manageable.
Had a setback with Xander's initial code. Memory management issues. Back to the drawing board, but I'm learning a lot from these mistakes.
Made progress with Xander's core functionality. Simple chatbot features are coming along. Got some friends to test it out, feedback was positive.
Spent the day exploring blockchain tech. How can I integrate this with Xander? The possibilities are intriguing, but complex.
Met up with an old friend from college. They're interested in Xander and offered to help with the visual design. Collaboration is key.
First successful integration of xAI's LLM into Xander. Basic, but it understands context now. Small victory, but it feels huge.
Had a job interview today. It didn't go as planned, but it's okay. I'm more focused on building Xander and exploring new career paths.
Working on a custom fine-tuning pipeline for Xander. It's about adapting the model for personal assistant use. Lots of trial and error.
Went to an AI ethics workshop. It's crucial to consider the implications of AI like Xander. Ethics will guide his development.
Xander's first NFT character sketch is done. It's simple, but it's a start. Excited to see where this visual aspect takes us.
